93	 * Check whether the given array is stored contiguously
94	 * in memory. And update the passed in ap flags appropriately.
95	 *
96	 * The traditional rule is that for an array to be flagged as C contiguous,
97	 * the following must hold:
98	 *
99	 * strides[-1] == itemsize
100	 * strides[i] == shape[i+1] * strides[i + 1]
101	 *
102	 * And for an array to be flagged as F contiguous, the obvious reversal:
103	 *
104	 * strides[0] == itemsize
105	 * strides[i] == shape[i - 1] * strides[i - 1]
106	 *
107	 * According to these rules, a 0- or 1-dimensional array is either both
108	 * C- and F-contiguous, or neither; and an array with 2+ dimensions
109	 * can be C- or F- contiguous, or neither, but not both (unless it has only
110	 * a single element).
111	 * We correct this, however.  When a dimension has length 1, its stride is
112	 * never used and thus has no effect on the  memory layout.
113	 * The above rules thus only apply when ignoring all size 1 dimensions.
114	 */
