26	/*************************************************************************
27	 * PEP 3118 buffer protocol
28	 *
29	 * Implementing PEP 3118 is somewhat convoluted because of the requirements:
30	 *
31	 * - Don't add new members to ndarray or descr structs, to preserve binary
32	 *   compatibility. (Also, adding the items is actually not very useful,
33	 *   since mutability issues prevent a one-to-one relationship between arrays
34	 *   and buffer views.)
35	 *
36	 * - Don't use bf_releasebuffer, because it prevents PyArg_ParseTuple("s#", ...
37	 *   from working. Breaking this would cause several backward compatibility
38	 *   issues already on Python 2.6.
39	 *
40	 * - Behave correctly when array is reshaped in-place, or it's dtype is
41	 *   altered.
42	 *
43	 * The solution taken below is to manually track memory allocated for
44	 * Py_buffers.
45	 *************************************************************************/
